1) How does Java achieve platform independence?
    ->  Using Java Compiler Java Code will compile into .class files or bytecode files
        and after that JVM will converted this .class file into machine language code thats Why Java is Platform Independant.

2) What is ClassLoader in Java?
    ->  ClassLoader is subsystem of JVM thats load the class file when we run java Progarms
        When we run java Progarms its loads the ClassLoader

